141
00:06:37,271 --> 00:06:39,145
With hair,

142
00:06:39,518 --> 00:06:42,050
I'll first go over things

143
00:06:42,052 --> 00:06:44,535
that are important when you divide hair.

144
00:06:45,293 --> 00:06:46,838
The important thing

145
00:06:46,863 --> 00:06:53,063
is first, you should think of the big parts

146
00:06:56,918 --> 00:06:58,426
and the small parts separately.

147
00:06:59,465 --> 00:07:00,767
In real life,

148
00:07:00,769 --> 00:07:03,833
our hair isn't all together

149
00:07:03,835 --> 00:07:05,142
in a neat form.

150
00:07:05,144 --> 00:07:07,621
A character would have lumps of hair.

151
00:07:07,754 --> 00:07:09,445
So, when we're describing hair,

152
00:07:09,469 --> 00:07:12,138
and if we don't divide it into big and small parts,

153
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:15,527
it will overall be poorly arranged.

154
00:07:15,552 --> 00:07:18,174
It will also be confusing

155
00:07:18,199 --> 00:07:19,859
how you should arrange the hair

156
00:07:19,883 --> 00:07:21,012
and how you should describe it

157
00:07:21,037 --> 00:07:22,426
while thinking of a specific hairstyle.

158
00:07:22,589 --> 00:07:25,197
So, dividing hair into big and small parts

159
00:07:25,199 --> 00:07:28,004
will have a big impact on important decisions later.

160
00:07:28,422 --> 00:07:30,144
Such as irregularity.

161
00:07:35,094 --> 00:07:36,170
I told you before

162
00:07:36,172 --> 00:07:38,650
that it is good to draw hair irregularly.

163
00:07:38,652 --> 00:07:43,135
If it is too neat, it won't look human.

164
00:07:45,151 --> 00:07:46,402
It will be unnatural

165
00:07:46,793 --> 00:07:47,806
and stiff.

166
00:07:47,808 --> 00:07:50,418
Many people will find it unnatural.

167
00:07:50,707 --> 00:07:52,722
It also won't have a nice aesthetic.

168
00:07:53,324 --> 00:07:55,990
Even design-wise, it is not good to have

169
00:07:56,015 --> 00:07:58,762
repetitive regular patterns.

170
00:07:58,926 --> 00:08:01,514
So, to add in irregular elements,

171
00:08:01,539 --> 00:08:04,335
we are dividing the hair

172
00:08:04,337 --> 00:08:06,808
into big and small parts.

173
00:08:07,038 --> 00:08:09,885
And, if we choose one more thing that's important,

174
00:08:09,887 --> 00:08:11,609
it's that they shouldn't be flat.

175
00:08:15,722 --> 00:08:17,315
Make the hair three-dimensional.

176
00:08:17,340 --> 00:08:20,137
For this concept,

177
00:08:20,755 --> 00:08:24,528
you might actually have heard of it before.

178
00:08:24,530 --> 00:08:27,441
The hair itself is like a huge side.

179
00:08:28,175 --> 00:08:32,229
And because it is covering the head,

180
00:08:32,254 --> 00:08:35,750
it is three-dimensional, not flat.

181
00:08:35,751 --> 00:08:38,024
You might have seen this concept

182
00:08:38,025 --> 00:08:40,389
in another lecture

183
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:42,799
or from a YouTube video.

184
00:08:42,801 --> 00:08:44,971
What I'm doing today is similar to that.

185
00:08:44,996 --> 00:08:46,190
However,

186
00:08:46,215 --> 00:08:49,660
I'll also tell you how to approach this more easily.

187
00:08:49,793 --> 00:08:52,121
In addition, I'll pinpoint

188
00:08:52,504 --> 00:08:56,316
where you should change your perception regarding the hair.

189
00:08:57,676 --> 00:08:59,470
So, let's get to it.

190
00:08:59,472 --> 00:09:00,972
I've mentioned that

191
00:09:01,418 --> 00:09:03,330
you should divide hair into big and small parts.

192
00:09:03,355 --> 00:09:06,666
The front hair, side hair, and the back hair,

193
00:09:06,691 --> 00:09:10,316
these three parts would be the big parts.

194
00:09:12,191 --> 00:09:14,629
So, would you just have to divide it randomly?

195
00:09:14,824 --> 00:09:17,799
Go for it if you're a pro.

196
00:09:17,824 --> 00:09:20,518
But, if you don't have much experience,

197
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:23,769
or if your hair is too simple

198
00:09:23,794 --> 00:09:25,866
or bland,

199
00:09:25,891 --> 00:09:29,245
divide the hair once more.

200
00:09:29,379 --> 00:09:33,949
You can divide the front hair into the part that goes between the eyes

201
00:09:35,222 --> 00:09:37,863
and the two parts next to it.

202
00:09:38,246 --> 00:09:41,135
Just make sure that the middle is wide

203
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,652
and the parts next to it are narrow.

204
00:09:42,894 --> 00:09:44,449
And here's the side hair.

205
00:09:44,613 --> 00:09:48,566
With the back hair, draw in this part.

206
00:09:48,824 --> 00:09:50,681
The reason behind this division is simple.

207
00:09:50,683 --> 00:09:53,027
If someone has long hair,

208
00:09:53,052 --> 00:09:55,566
this hair here would go behind their ears.

209
00:09:55,832 --> 00:09:57,018
So, usually,

210
00:09:57,043 --> 00:09:59,816
the hair here would go right down,

211
00:09:59,926 --> 00:10:03,879
while the hair here has to avoid the air.

212
00:10:03,904 --> 00:10:05,921
That's why the hair flow would be different.

213
00:10:06,051 --> 00:10:08,887
So, we would divide a part here,

214
00:10:10,371 --> 00:10:14,472
and you would keep dividing it into more parts

215
00:10:15,051 --> 00:10:17,613
depending on the situation.

216
00:10:17,638 --> 00:10:20,504
Now let's divide it into even smaller parts.

217
00:10:21,586 --> 00:10:22,722
Like this.

218
00:10:25,385 --> 00:10:26,558
And again.

219
00:10:31,097 --> 00:10:34,152
It is important to divide it randomly.

220
00:10:34,347 --> 00:10:37,402
If you don't do so intentionally,

221
00:10:37,427 --> 00:10:39,941
you'll end up with hair that is too regular.

222
00:10:40,621 --> 00:10:42,910
This is a common mistake

223
00:10:42,935 --> 00:10:44,988
that male artists make.

224
00:10:46,988 --> 00:10:51,793
If you're good at drawing machines,

225
00:10:51,818 --> 00:10:55,441
but have difficulty drawing nature, like trees,

226
00:10:55,466 --> 00:10:58,676
you might also come across this mistake

227
00:10:58,701 --> 00:11:00,879
where you'd draw hair too evenly.

228
00:11:00,904 --> 00:11:02,949
So, you should be aware of that.

229
00:11:02,950 --> 00:11:07,121
You should intentionally divide hair randomly.

230
00:11:07,146 --> 00:11:08,375
That's important.

231
00:11:09,051 --> 00:11:12,269
So, let's say we're dividing it irregularly.

232
00:11:12,294 --> 00:11:15,519
But is there a shortcut to it?

233
00:11:16,972 --> 00:11:18,629
I'll give you some advice.

234
00:11:18,654 --> 00:11:21,613
Stick a small part to a big part.

235
00:11:23,004 --> 00:11:24,597
For instance, like this.

236
00:11:24,898 --> 00:11:29,371
I'll add a small part, and a big part again.

237
00:11:32,782 --> 00:11:35,557
And then a big part, and a small part.

238
00:11:35,559 --> 00:11:38,730
You can take turns with the big part and the small part.

239
00:11:38,755 --> 00:11:41,121
Or, you can just draw a big part in the middle.

240
00:11:41,286 --> 00:11:44,030
You can draw in multiple small parts, too.

241
00:11:44,418 --> 00:11:46,697
So, if you randomly draw these parts,

242
00:11:46,699 --> 00:11:49,941
your hair will look much more natural.

243
00:11:50,754 --> 00:11:52,334
Draw a small part next to a big part.

244
00:11:52,335 --> 00:11:54,404
That's what I commonly do.

245
00:11:54,406 --> 00:11:56,887
It's also what I commonly recommend to students.

246
00:11:58,937 --> 00:12:02,387
You would draw in smaller parts like this.

247
00:12:08,074 --> 00:12:10,244
For now, don't focus on the hairstyle.

248
00:12:10,269 --> 00:12:11,801
Focus on dividing the hair into smaller parts.

249
00:12:12,379 --> 00:12:14,816
I'll tell you how to draw different hairstyles

250
00:12:15,301 --> 00:12:17,426
later on.

251
00:12:19,005 --> 00:12:21,707
Make sure the side hair

252
00:12:23,310 --> 00:12:25,512
covers the front hair.

253
00:12:29,206 --> 00:12:31,042
A small part, and a big part.

254
00:12:31,419 --> 00:12:32,418
Then a small part.

255
00:12:36,295 --> 00:12:37,488
The same goes for long hair, too.

256
00:12:39,620 --> 00:12:42,222
A small part, and then a big part.

257
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:44,004
Another small part.

258
00:12:45,586 --> 00:12:46,558
And another one.

259
00:12:47,334 --> 00:12:48,933
Make sure you take turns with drawing

260
00:12:54,894 --> 00:12:58,276
the big part and the small part.

261
00:12:58,301 --> 00:13:00,199
That's how you would draw hair.

262
00:13:00,987 --> 00:13:03,902
Now that I've drawn in the overall shape,

263
00:13:05,525 --> 00:13:08,713
I'll add the hair strands as well.

264
00:13:08,957 --> 00:13:12,213
I'll give you a tip with hair strands.

265
00:13:12,214 --> 00:13:16,152
Hair strands are basically single hairs sticking out.

266
00:13:16,177 --> 00:13:19,519
So, it's good to know when hair looks irregular.

267
00:13:20,019 --> 00:13:22,035
When does that happen?

268
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,402
It happens when it gets blown in the wind.

269
