00:27:38,774 --> 00:27:41,849
make sure that the hair goes outwards

575
00:27:43,006 --> 00:27:44,927
and that the silhouette has some irregularity.

576
00:27:48,005 --> 00:27:50,293
Let's experiment with it a lot

577
00:27:50,318 --> 00:27:52,411
and approach drawing different hairstyles.

578
00:27:52,911 --> 00:27:55,568
Now, let's look at this male character's face.

579
00:27:55,593 --> 00:27:58,371
Some of you may think that a male character's hairstyle

580
00:27:58,396 --> 00:28:00,843
is harder to approach than a female character's hairstyle.

581
00:28:00,845 --> 00:28:01,994
Why does that happen?

582
00:28:01,995 --> 00:28:04,404
Generally, a male character has short hair.

583
00:28:04,599 --> 00:28:06,155
Of course, not all of them have short hair.

584
00:28:06,157 --> 00:28:08,631
But when we are drawing short hair,

585
00:28:08,633 --> 00:28:11,297
dividing the hair into smaller parts

586
00:28:11,679 --> 00:28:12,974
is more challenging.

587
00:28:13,138 --> 00:28:15,997
Dividing it into big parts is the same.

588
00:28:17,404 --> 00:28:18,519
With short hair, too,

589
00:28:18,544 --> 00:28:19,728
we would divide it into the front hair,

590
00:28:19,752 --> 00:28:22,068
the side hair, and the back hair.

591
00:28:25,194 --> 00:28:27,599
I'll keep it short since I'm drawing short hair.

592
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:34,646
Dividing it into big parts is the same.

593
00:28:34,810 --> 00:28:39,294
But, after that, it becomes a bit complicated.

594
00:28:41,085 --> 00:28:42,724
Why is it complicated?

595
00:28:44,193 --> 00:28:46,138
When I was dividing it,

596
00:28:46,450 --> 00:28:48,758
see how I connected them with a same line?

597
00:28:48,760 --> 00:28:51,779
When we look at hair from the side,

598
00:28:53,825 --> 00:28:55,738
our hair

599
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:57,271
doesn't just have this part

600
00:28:57,296 --> 00:28:59,208
and nothing underneath.

601
00:28:59,310 --> 00:29:01,082
If there's nothing underneath, when we jump,

602
00:29:01,107 --> 00:29:02,880
this hair would fly like this

603
00:29:03,215 --> 00:29:04,630
and there would be no hair in this area.

604
00:29:05,849 --> 00:29:07,607
So, how does our hair actually look?

605
00:29:07,632 --> 00:29:09,414
In real life, with hair,

606
00:29:09,591 --> 00:29:12,036
if there's hair at the top, there's hair underneath it.

607
00:29:12,161 --> 00:29:13,106
There's some more hair underneath that,

608
00:29:13,108 --> 00:29:14,089
and some more underneath.

609
00:29:14,091 --> 00:29:15,654
Like this.

610
00:29:15,679 --> 00:29:17,021
In other words, it's layered.

611
00:29:17,663 --> 00:29:20,357
With female characters, this is not that evident.

612
00:29:20,382 --> 00:29:22,163
Because if we have the upper hair,

613
00:29:22,188 --> 00:29:23,567
it covers everything up,

614
00:29:23,591 --> 00:29:25,107
so we can't see the hair underneath it.

615
00:29:25,219 --> 00:29:26,091
Because it is long.

616
00:29:26,185 --> 00:29:29,222
But, with male characters, if they have short hair,

617
00:29:29,224 --> 00:29:31,454
the hair underneath it can be seen.

618
00:29:31,456 --> 00:29:32,708
This also happens with female characters with short hair.

619
00:29:32,733 --> 00:29:36,099
Because the hair underneath can be seen,

620
00:29:37,544 --> 00:29:40,674
we draw it as if it's layered.

621
00:29:40,676 --> 00:29:43,286
So, as you divide it into big and small parts,

622
00:29:48,919 --> 00:29:51,503
you need to make sure to layer them.

623
00:29:53,508 --> 00:29:54,682
A big part

624
00:29:55,794 --> 00:29:57,002
then a small part,

625
00:29:57,089 --> 00:29:58,366
a small part,

626
00:29:58,612 --> 00:29:59,809
then a big part.

627
00:29:59,891 --> 00:30:01,230
Draw them alternately.

628
00:30:04,818 --> 00:30:05,925
Draw in a small part.

629
00:30:07,114 --> 00:30:10,167
Draw some more small parts

630
00:30:10,192 --> 00:30:11,573
because it has short hair.

631
00:30:14,995 --> 00:30:17,190
Make sure it looks like

632
00:30:17,215 --> 00:30:19,029
there are more parts added in irregularly.

633
00:30:21,807 --> 00:30:23,155
Like I did previously,

634
00:30:23,179 --> 00:30:25,076
I'll add hair to this.

635
00:30:28,341 --> 00:30:29,628
Before I begin,

636
00:30:32,518 --> 00:30:34,151
I'll have to divide these parts again.

637
00:30:34,176 --> 00:30:35,526
A small part,

638
00:30:36,855 --> 00:30:37,870
then a big part,

639
00:30:40,802 --> 00:30:42,682
a big part, then a small part.

640
00:30:43,596 --> 00:30:45,081
Draw in some more hair here.

641
00:30:45,186 --> 00:30:47,003
A small part, then a big part.

642
00:30:54,380 --> 00:30:56,425
Another small part here.

643
00:30:57,050 --> 00:30:58,788
Draw in additional parts

644
00:30:58,812 --> 00:31:00,943
and make sure they look irregular.

645
00:31:01,214 --> 00:31:02,181
A small part,

646
00:31:02,206 --> 00:31:03,120
then a big part.

647
00:31:03,145 --> 00:31:05,811
Then, you can add

648
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:08,040
irregularity to it.

649
00:31:08,042 --> 00:31:10,409
Then, the hair won't look unnatural

650
00:31:10,434 --> 00:31:11,651
and it won't look stiff.

651
00:31:11,676 --> 00:31:14,284
That can be avoided,

652
00:31:15,268 --> 00:31:18,596
and you'll be able to draw natural-looking hair.

653
00:31:18,893 --> 00:31:21,534
So, most people who find it difficult to draw hair say that

654
00:31:21,536 --> 00:31:23,374
they have trouble with the parts

655
00:31:23,398 --> 00:31:24,898
that are too regular.

656
00:31:24,923 --> 00:31:26,620
There are also people

657
00:31:26,621 --> 00:31:28,714
who draw hair too regularly

658
00:31:29,135 --> 00:31:30,806
without realizing it until the end.

659
00:31:30,831 --> 00:31:34,213
So, make sure you check after you draw everything.

660
00:31:34,215 --> 00:31:36,789
It is really important to check

661
00:31:36,791 --> 00:31:39,314
if the hair has little to no irregularity.

662
00:31:39,316 --> 00:31:41,284
I call this self-feedback.

663
00:31:41,382 --> 00:31:44,689
You should give yourself feedback in your work process

664
00:31:44,714 --> 00:31:46,743
whether you're drawing a human body

665
00:31:46,745 --> 00:31:48,721
or an illustration whenever possible.

666
00:31:49,331 --> 00:31:51,198
People usually don't do this if they aren't told to.

667
00:31:51,307 --> 00:31:53,338
People usually do this

668
00:31:53,340 --> 00:31:55,518
a long time after they've finished a drawing.

669
00:31:55,737 --> 00:31:57,952
At that point, they'll feel

670
00:31:58,182 --> 00:31:59,900
as if they didn't do a good job on it.

671
00:31:59,902 --> 00:32:03,821
Or, right before completion, you may think your drawing looks terrible.

672
00:32:03,822 --> 00:32:05,206
So you might not want to finish it.

673
00:32:06,296 --> 00:32:07,793
To prevent this from happening,

674
00:32:07,818 --> 00:32:13,198
it is very important to

675
00:32:13,901 --> 00:32:16,214
do self-feedback as you're drawing.

676
00:32:16,925 --> 00:32:19,579
In that process, make sure

677
00:32:19,604 --> 00:32:22,706
that your hair has enough regularity and irregularity

678
00:32:22,948 --> 00:32:23,962
and that they are used alternately.

679
00:32:23,987 --> 00:32:25,741
So, I'll draw this male character's hair

680
00:32:25,765 --> 00:32:27,784
by drawing many layers in it.

681
00:32:30,620 --> 00:32:33,151
It looks complicated, doesn't it?

682
00:32:33,401 --> 00:32:35,940
So, when you're drawing natural-looking hair,

683
00:32:35,973 --> 00:32:38,616
I think that it is more difficult to

684
00:32:38,640 --> 00:32:40,034
draw a male character's hair.

685
00:32:43,315 --> 00:32:46,104
But, if you color this layered hair well,

686
00:32:46,129 --> 00:32:48,221
it will look really natural

687
00:32:49,603 --> 00:32:51,753
and it will look more aesthetic.

688
00:32:52,884 --> 00:32:55,513
That doesn't mean long hair isn't aesthetic.

689
00:32:56,323 --> 00:32:59,877
We approach it with the same method when we perm a male character's hair.

690
00:32:59,902 --> 00:33:02,143
We approach it in the same way,

691
00:33:05,907 --> 00:33:08,526
but we can't quite flip the hair since it's short.

692
00:33:10,300 --> 00:33:11,600
It will be difficult to

693
00:33:11,601 --> 00:33:12,753
flip it more than twice.

694
00:33:12,754 --> 00:33:14,831
Even when you're flipping it, flip it just once.

695
00:33:17,546 --> 00:33:19,214
An upper side, and an underside.

696
00:33:20,831 --> 00:33:23,290
So the part that bends once becomes twice or

697
00:33:24,453 --> 00:33:26,387
the part that went backwards goes forwards

698
00:33:26,906 --> 00:33:28,800
and vice versa.

699
00:33:30,211 --> 00:33:32,307
So make some changes

700
00:33:32,795 --> 00:33:34,792
to add perm to the hair.

701
00:33:36,001 --> 00:33:37,237
Twist it around.

702
00:33:54,784 --> 00:33:57,295
This is how you should approach

703
00:33:57,319 --> 00:33:59,166
a character's hairstyle.

704
00:33:59,191 --> 00:34:00,255
One more thing.

705
00:34:00,280 --> 00:34:03,619
Let's also learn how to draw hair blowing in the wind.

706
00:34:03,644 --> 00:34:06,675
Like I mentioned before, hair blowing in the wind

707
00:34:06,700 --> 00:34:10,844
would make an S shape and blow around.

708
00:34:10,846 --> 00:34:12,012
Again, here,

709
00:34:12,014 --> 00:34:15,916
there are parts with irregularity.

710
00:34:17,713 --> 00:34:22,799
If a big part flows like this,

711
00:34:24,252 --> 00:34:27,373
we would add in smaller parts,

712
00:34:27,375 --> 00:34:30,557
then we would flip the hair

713
00:34:36,940 --> 00:34:39,643
and there would be irregularity because the hair flow would change too.

714
00:34:39,668 --> 00:34:42,518
There's always irregularity to parts where the flow changes.

715
00:34:43,841 --> 00:34:47,799
Add in hair strands, too.

716
00:34:53,680 --> 00:34:55,002
Small and big ones.

717
00:34:59,041 --> 00:35:00,682
Approach the front hair in the same way.

718
00:35:01,041 --> 00:35:02,479
Small part, then a big part.

719
00:35:03,088 --> 00:35:05,104
Small, small and big.

720
00:35:08,824 --> 00:35:10,104
Flip it over,

721
00:35:10,899 --> 00:35:12,315
and add irregularity.

722
00:35:14,096 --> 00:35:16,580
Once you are familiar with it,

723
00:35:16,764 --> 00:35:18,573
draw them alternately.

724
00:35:18,598 --> 00:35:23,252
If you do this a lot, it will be detailed and the character will look mature.

725
00:35:23,596 --> 00:35:26,155
But if you don't do this a lot,

726
00:35:26,179 --> 00:35:28,347
it will be a more casual style character.

727
00:35:28,349 --> 00:35:30,585
So, you can decide how much you'll do this depending on

728
00:35:30,587 --> 00:35:32,416
your drawing style and your character's personality.

729
00:35:45,515 --> 00:35:47,889
You may ask why I'm emphasizing this.

