00:35:47,891 --> 00:35:49,726
How much would a character's atmosphere change

731
00:35:51,101 --> 00:35:52,820
depending on how much the hair is deformed?

732
00:35:53,134 --> 00:35:54,570
Well, there's a big difference!

733
00:35:55,031 --> 00:35:59,027
Even if the wind is blowing in the same way,

734
00:35:59,029 --> 00:36:01,140
this detailed hair above

735
00:36:08,524 --> 00:36:11,398
and this less detailed hair below,

736
00:36:14,197 --> 00:36:16,999
you can see that they each give off

737
00:36:23,046 --> 00:36:24,406
different atmospheres.

738
00:36:24,408 --> 00:36:26,710
I'm not trying to say that the one on the bottom has less detail.

739
00:36:32,309 --> 00:36:34,736
See how they have a different feeling?

740
00:36:34,738 --> 00:36:38,518
With the amount of hair strands, think of the mood you want to create,

741
00:36:38,543 --> 00:36:41,111
and add in the amount you want.

742
00:36:42,279 --> 00:36:44,901
Now, we're done with studying hair for now.

743
00:36:45,010 --> 00:36:48,088
To sum up... With hair, you need to divide it into big and small parts

744
00:36:48,113 --> 00:36:50,992
to add irregularity.

745
00:36:51,401 --> 00:36:53,709
And, if you want to focus on the volume as well,

746
00:36:53,711 --> 00:36:59,314
note that the hair itself is a dimension.

747
00:36:59,316 --> 00:37:03,080
Make sure the hair covers the head,

748
00:37:03,197 --> 00:37:06,518
then, you can draw natural looking hair.

749
00:37:06,916 --> 00:37:10,086
And, remember the parts that add irregularity to the hair

750
00:37:10,111 --> 00:37:12,815
and the hair designs commonly used for casual style characters.

751
00:37:15,065 --> 00:37:17,876
When the hair blows in the wind,

752
00:37:17,878 --> 00:37:19,443
flip it over

753
00:37:19,445 --> 00:37:21,127
to give it irregular elements.

754
00:37:21,557 --> 00:37:23,711
If you focus on that,

755
00:37:23,712 --> 00:37:25,299
you can successfully draw

756
00:37:25,301 --> 00:37:28,488
a charming hairstyle.

757
00:37:28,513 --> 00:37:31,700
Of course, there are numerous hairstyles in real life.

758
00:37:31,725 --> 00:37:36,110
To practice drawing them, it's best to use photo references.

759
00:37:36,830 --> 00:37:38,550
There are hairstyles that actually exist,

760
00:37:38,552 --> 00:37:39,975
but there are also hairstyles

761
00:37:39,977 --> 00:37:42,383
that only exist in illustrations.

762
00:37:42,408 --> 00:37:44,174
Analyzing them can be a fun exercise.

763
00:37:44,315 --> 00:37:45,290
But, when you're analyzing them,

764
00:37:45,292 --> 00:37:49,197
make sure you divide the hair

765
00:37:49,244 --> 00:37:50,899
into the side, back and front parts.

766
00:37:50,924 --> 00:37:53,079
If you do that,

767
00:37:53,104 --> 00:37:55,104
you'll be able to analyze it more efficiently.

768
00:37:55,424 --> 00:37:58,401
So, that was what I wanted to emphasize.

