00:38:47,807 --> 00:38:50,204
although it's okay to sketch with lines,

788
00:38:50,206 --> 00:38:52,449
it's best to study with dimensions.

789
00:38:52,451 --> 00:38:53,244
But why?

790
00:38:53,269 --> 00:38:54,815
What exactly are creases on clothes?

791
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:56,307
Basically, you would think

792
00:38:56,549 --> 00:38:58,945
that they are folds in the clothing.

793
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:01,080
But, you should note that

794
00:39:01,105 --> 00:39:03,408
even the half-folded parts are creases, too.

795
00:39:04,088 --> 00:39:05,455
What does that mean?

796
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:08,162
Because these creases

797
00:39:08,187 --> 00:39:09,978
aren't really just lines.

798
00:39:09,980 --> 00:39:11,760
See how it's shaded?

799
00:39:12,890 --> 00:39:15,446
This part becomes dark

800
00:39:15,471 --> 00:39:18,041
because

801
00:39:18,526 --> 00:39:19,946
when we separate it into different dimensions,

802
00:39:19,948 --> 00:39:22,493
this front area receives a lot of light.

803
00:39:22,506 --> 00:39:26,359
On the other hand, these two dimensions receive less light

804
00:39:26,373 --> 00:39:27,908
because they're on the side.

805
00:39:28,322 --> 00:39:30,298
So, with creases, they are very three-dimensional,

806
00:39:30,299 --> 00:39:33,315
and have a lot to do with light and shade.

807
00:39:33,963 --> 00:39:35,665
So, when you're drawing creases,

808
00:39:35,690 --> 00:39:37,529
don't draw them as lines,

809
00:39:37,531 --> 00:39:40,157
but as dimensions instead.

810
00:39:40,159 --> 00:39:41,432
It would be much more effective.

811
00:39:41,713 --> 00:39:43,848
So, if you want to practice creases,

812
00:39:43,850 --> 00:39:46,329
